    "en": {
      "title": "Agricultural representatives beat urea with hammer",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Farmers have alleged that some representatives of farmers' organizations are running a racket of collecting money from them as rent of 250, 300, 500, 1000 rupees for each bundle of fertilizer during the supply of urea fertilizer by the government to the farmers in Polonnaruwa.",
        "The farmers point out that they unload the bales of fertilizer themselves, and even though they do so, some representatives of farmers' organizations are doing unfair things by charging them money as rent for unloading the urea fertilizer.",
        "The farmers also mention that the farmers' organizations such as Manampitiya, Dalukana, Alleweva, Sanshiyya, Maguldamana have collected 250 to 1000 rupees as unloading rent.",
        "That power cut was allowed for 2 hours and 30 minutes from 6.00 am to 8.30 am for Colombo cities and AITCC category, and for 3 hours from 5.00 am to 8.00 am for M, N, O, X, Y and Z zones. Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission Mr. Janaka Ratnayake said further."
      ],
